x3375+0+313/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F88%2F9d1ef5844af4b8e3ea5a53ab9cb0%2Fgettyimages-2221263333.jpg" class="img" alt="Andrew Cuomo speaks during an election party following the primaries at the Carpenters Union in New York City on June 24, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Andrew Cuomo speaks during an election party following the primaries at the Carpenters Union in New York City on June 24, 2025.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          John Lamparski/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo announced yesterday that he is &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/news/andrew-cuomo-relaunches-campaign-for-mayor-after-losing-primary-to-zohran-mamdani" target="_blank"&gt;relaunching his campaign&lt;/a&gt; for New York City mayor, this time as an independent candidate. (via &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Gothamist&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;South African President Cyril Ramaphosa has suspended his police minister after serious allegations &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/14/nx-s1-5467245/south-africa-police-corruption-scandal-ramaphosa" target="_blank"&gt;linking him to organized crime&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Los Angeles is now three years away from the Olympic Games, and to commemorate the occasion, organizers yesterday &lt;a href="https://laist.com/news/los-angeles-activities/la-olympics-schedule-first-look" target="_blank"&gt;released a preview of the competition schedule&lt;/a&gt;. (via &lt;a href="https://laist.com/" target="_blank"&gt;LAist&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
