stling-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7269x4088+0+380/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2F03%2F7a2630bc49909c9de68648e8c06a%2Fmcbryde-wrestling-1.jpg" class="img" alt="Jamilah McBryde works up a sweat to cut weight in preparation for the 2025 National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics (NAIA) Women&amp;#039;s Wrestling National Championship, hosted in Wichita, Kan., in March." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Jamilah McBryde works up a sweat to cut weight in preparation for the 2025 National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics (NAIA) Women's Wrestling National Championship, hosted in Wichita, Kan., in March.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Geoff Stellfox for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jamilah, Zaynah, and Latifah McBryde are sisters from Buffalo, N.Y., who grew up wrestling each other. They never expected to become college athletes. Although coaches recognized their talent as teenagers, they faced challenges wearing the required wrestling singlet due to their Muslim faith. However, their passion for the sport and determination led to changes in the rules, allowing Muslim women to compete in full-body uniforms at both collegiate and national levels. Their uniforms have evolved over the years and now include Velcro to keep their shirts tucked into their pants and tape to secure their hijabs. While these modest uniforms honor their faith, they have also sparked controversy throughout their journey in the sport. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/07/11/nx-s1-5436073/womens-wrestling-sports-muslim-uniforms" target="_blank"&gt;Read more and see photos of how&lt;/a&gt; the sisters have helped change the sport.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-77407" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4384;         --source-height: 2466;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4384x2466+0+287/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa0%2F4d%2Fec6ca7474baf9de17af5d54352e5%2Fgettyimages-2224313149.jpg" class="img" alt="Italy&amp;#039;s Jannik Sinner celebrates after victory against Spain&amp;#039;s Carlos Alcaraz at Wimbledon, southwest London, on Sunday." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Italy's Jannik Sinner celebrates after victory against Spain's Carlos Alcaraz at Wimbledon, southwest London, on Sunday.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kirill Kudryavtsev/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Jannik Sinner, a 23-year-old from Italy, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/13/nx-s1-5466312/jannik-sinner-wimbledon-carlos-alcaraz" target="_blank"&gt;won the men's singles championship&lt;/a&gt; at Wimbledon yesterday. The victory marks the country's first singles champion at the tournament.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grand Canyon National Park officials say the fast-moving Dragon Bravo Fire &lt;a href="https://www.knau.org/knau-and-arizona-news/2025-07-13/north-rim-fire-leads-to-poison-gas-leak-phantom-ranch-evacuated" target="_blank"&gt;destroyed the historic lodge on the North Rim&lt;/a&gt;, along with several other structures, over the weekend. (via &lt;a href="https://www.knau.org/" target="_blank"&gt;KNAU&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Nigeria's former president Muhammadu Buhari &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/13/nx-s1-5466180/nigerias-former-president-muhammadu-buhari-dies-at-82" target="_blank"&gt;has died at a hospital&lt;/a&gt; in London at the age of 82, a spokesperson confirmed yesterday.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
